data problem\nforge/docs/ai-workflow-testing.md:74:- the `fix-missing-reachability-metadata` skill usage is relevant and not replaced by random exploration\nforge/docs/ai-workflow-testing.md:75:- the proposed metadata changes match the failing native image evidence\nforge/docs/ai-workflow-testing.md:79:If the metadata-fix stage times out, treat that as a concrete workflow problem and review the log before changing prompts or strategy settings.\nforge/docs/ai-workflow-testing.md:89:- the metadata output is present and consistent with the test outcome\nforge/docs/ai-workflow-testing.md:91:- nothing in the generated output suggests the agent solved the task by breaking or trivializing the test\nforge/docs/ai-workflow-testing.md:110:- `metrics.metadata_entries`\nforge/docs/ai-workflow-testing.md:111:- `metrics.test_only_metadata_entries` when test-only metadata exists\nforge/docs/ai-workflow-testing.md:113:- `artifacts.metadata_file`\nforge/docs/ai-workflow-testing.md:115:Coverage and other metrics do not need a single universal threshold, but they must look credible for the library size and the generated test shape. Suspiciously low coverage, near-empty tests, or inflated metadata with weak tests should be treated as failures that need investigation.\nforge/docs/ai-workflow-testing.md:126:- if metadata-fix ran, its log also looks valid\nforge/docs/ai-workflow-testing.md:136:- metadata-fix times out or behaves incoherently\nforge/docs/ai-workflow-testing.md:142:Unit tests for agent adapters, strategy loading, and small helpers are still useful, but they are secondary checks.\nforge/docs/ai-workflow-testing.md:148:- reviewing metadata-fix logs\nforge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:5:> [Native metadata exploration phase](../docs/native-metadata-exploration.md) ·\nforge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:29:  [--reachability-metadata-path /path/to/graalvm-reachability-metadata] \\\nforge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:41:  [--reachability-metadata-path /path/to/graalvm-reachability-metadata] \\\nforge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:64:3. Send the prompt to the configured agent.\nforge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:67:6. Send subsequent failure output back to the agent until success or `max-test-iterations`.\nforge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:68:7. Use the same finalization path to generate metadata, validate tests, collect stats, and commit.\nforge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:85:- whether to skip agent prompting if the initial test already reaches `nativeTest` or passes\nforge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:96:- metadata index and version directory setup\nforge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:98:- strategy and agent initialization\nforge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:109:3. **Project preparation**: copy old version dir, update `gradle.properties`, create metadata dir, git checkpoint.\nforge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:114:8. **Run workflow**: `strategy_obj.run(agent)`.\nforge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:154:  \"agent\": \"pi\",\nforge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:170:### Forge metadata integration\nforge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:172:`forge_metadata.py` dispatches Java version-bump failures through the unified entry point:\nforge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:184:- stages the versioned tests, metadata index, metadata version directory, and stats\nforge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:196:### Forge metadata\nforge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:198:We need to wire these new changes with the forge_metadata.py and do_my_work scripts\nforge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:200:### Integration with the native metadata exploration phase\nforge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:204:[Native Metadata Exploration phase](../docs/native-metadata-exploration.md)\nforge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:205:as its **first corrective action**, before invoking the agent. This catches\nforge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:207:reachability metadata for the new library version.\nforge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:211:    NTFail[nativeTest fails] --> Explore[run_native_metadata_exploration]\nforge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:215:    Verify -- fail --> Codex[run_codex_metadata_fix<br/>with output_dir + result.failure]\nforge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:218:    Codex -- still fails --> Agent[Hand off to agent with raw nativeTest output]\nforge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:224:  `BUILD_FAILED`. A failed exploration may indicate a non-metadata code\nforge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:226:  metadata-tracing flags, or a runtime crash unrelated to missing\nforge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:227:  metadata. Codex receives the merged `output_dir` (possibly empty or\nforge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:230:  [docs/native-metadata-exploration.md §9](../docs/native-metadata-exploration.md).\nforge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:231:- The agent is invoked only when codex fixup, given those inputs, still\nforge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:242:After the agent (or the configured post-generation intervention) produces\nforge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:247:`./gradlew generateMetadata -Pcoordinates=<g:a:v> --agentAllowedPackages=fromJar`,\nforge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:250:budget, times out, or fails for a non-metadata reason, Codex is the final\nforge/docs/architecture.md:16:├─ forge_metadata.py           # Top-level dispatcher (issues, PRs, reviews)\nforge/docs/architecture.md:22:│  ├─ fix_metadata_codex.py        # Post-gen: Codex metadata repair\nforge/docs/architecture.md:24:│  ├─ agents/                      # Pluggable LLM agents (pi, codex)\nforge/docs/architecture.md:29:│  └─ predefined_strategies.json   # Named agent + workflow + prompts bundles\nforge/docs/architecture.md:42:        Dispatcher[\"forge_metadata.py<br/>(dispatcher)\"]\nforge/docs/architecture.md:67:        IntCodex[\"codex_then_pi (default)<br/>fix_metadata_codex → fix_post_generation_pi\"]\nforge/docs/architecture.md:68:        IntTrace[\"native_trace_collect<br/>native_metadata_exploration → codex\"]\nforge/docs/architecture.md:129:  commands through `agent.run_test_command(...)` and analyze the combined\nforge/docs/architecture.md:133:  library's `metadata/<group>/<artifact>