ub.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata)\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:11:code-generation agents with the repo's own build, test, and reporting\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:12:pipelines to produce metadata, tests, and PRs ready for human review.\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:19:   Kotlin/Scala) test suite, produce reachability metadata, and open a PR for\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:28:   reachability metadata so `nativeTest` passes against the new library\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:29:   version, using the native metadata exploration phase.\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:37:Out of scope: anything that does not produce reachability metadata or its\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:44:| **Reachability metadata** | JSON describing reflection, JNI, resource, serialization, and proxy access for a library, consumed by GraalVM `native-image`. |\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:45:| **Reachability repo** | Local checkout or worktree of `oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata`. The build and metadata-generation Gradle tasks run inside it. The parent checkout of `forge/` is used by default. |\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:48:| **Agent** | LLM-driven code editor (Aider, Codex, or Pi) registered through [ai_workflows/agents/](../ai_workflows/agents/). Each implements `send_prompt`, `run_test_command`, `clear_context`. |\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:50:| **Predefined strategy** | Named, fully parameterized combination of agent + workflow strategy + prompts + parameters in [strategies/predefined_strategies.json](../strategies/predefined_strategies.json). Selected via `--strategy-name`. |\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:53:| **Dynamic-access report** | JSON written by Gradle task `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport` to `tests/src/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`, listing classes and per-class call sites that require dynamic-access metadata, marked covered/uncovered. |\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:54:| **Source con