cs root is the same worktree's `forge/` directory.\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:21:- Local clone of https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:25:- Python 3 and the tooling required by the agent strategy you plan to run.\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:26:- Strategies with `\"graphify-context\": true` require graphify to be installed for the selected agent backend. Install docs: https://github.com/safishamsi/graphify#install\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:43:- Create/update the versioned test module in reachability-metadata.\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:44:- Run Gradle tests and, if native test fails, collect metadata and re-run.\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:52:  [--reachability-metadata-path /path/to/graalvm-reachability-metadata] \\\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:62:- `--reachability-metadata-path`: optional path to a graalvm-reachability-metadata worktree. If omitted, the parent checkout is used.\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:64:- `--docs-path`: optional directory with read-only docs for agent context (e.g., extracted Javadoc).\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:71:  --reachability-metadata-path /path/to/graalvm-reachability-metadata \\\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:78:- `-v`, `--verbose` enable verbose agent output.\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:81:- Runs Gradle tasks inside the reachability-metadata repo (`./gradlew ...`).\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:90:- Keep indices up to date and create the versioned metadata directory.\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:91:- Generates metadata for the new library.\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:99:  [--reachability-metadata-path /path/to/graalvm-reachability-metadata] \\\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:108:- `--reachability-metadata-path`: optional path to a graalvm-reachability-metadata worktree. If omitted, the parent checkout is used.\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:110:- `--docs-path`: optional directory with read-only docs for agent context (e.g., extracted Javadoc).\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:116:  --reachability-metadata-path /path/to/graalvm-reachability-metadata \\\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:122:- `--strategy-name NAME` select a predefined workflow strategy from `strategies/predefined_strategies.json`. Defaults to `basic_iterative_pi_gpt-5.4` (Pi agent).\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:124:- `-v`, `--verbose` enable verbose agent output.\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:127:- Runs Gradle tasks inside the reachability-metadata repo (`./gradlew ...`).\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:134:Description: Push changes to your fork/branch and open a PR against oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata.\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:141:  [--reachability-metadata-path /path/to/graalvm-reachability-metadata] \\\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:150:  --reachability-metadata-path /path/to/graalvm-reachability-metadata \\\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:162:Description: Push changes that add support for a new library and open a PR against oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata.\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:168:  [--reachability-metadata-path /path/to/graalvm-reachability-metadata] \\\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:176:  --reachability-metadata-path /path/to/graalvm-reachability-metadata \\\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:195:  [--reachability-metadata-path /path/to/graalvm-reachability-metadata] \\\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:212:  [--reachability-metadata-path /path/to/graalvm-reachability-metadata] \\\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:225:- Cleans up existing tests/metadata in the reachability-metadata repo for provided coordinates\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:238:  [--reachability-metadata-path /path/to/graalvm-reachability-metadata] \\\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:245:- `--reachability-metadata-path`: optional path to a `graalvm-reachability-metadata` worktree. If omitted, the parent checkout is used.\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:253:  python3 utility_scripts/count_reachability_entries.py /path/to/reachability-metadata.json\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:257:  python3 utility_scripts/count_native_image_config_entries.py /path/to/metadata/versioned/dir\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:268:Agents are registered via `Agent.register(...)` and selected per-strategy through the `agent` field in `strategies/predefined_strategies.json`. Supported agents:\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:270:- `pi` — default for the shipped strategies. Driven through `pi --mode rpc` by `PiAgent` (`ai_workflows/agents/pi_agent.py`). Per-turn transcripts are written to `logs/pi-<action>-<library>-<timestamp>.log` in this repository (see `utility_scripts/pi_logs.py`). Pi session files are stored under Pi's default session directory (`--session-dir` may override it via `PiRpcClient`). Select with strategy entries whose `agent` is `\"pi\"`; set `\"provider\": \"openrouter\"` to route through OpenRouter.\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:292:      agent=None,  # Agent implementation exposing token counters\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:337:- When a script utilizes an AI agent or inner process, implement the verbose flag `-v`, `--verbose` for easier tracing and debugging.\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:338:- If a script performs technical changes to the graalvm-reachability-metadata repository (tests, metadata, Gradle tasks, CI logic), implement and contribute that logic in that repository.\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:344:The project uses registry-based workflow and agent abstractions. Each workflow strategy is a Python class that inherits from `WorkflowStrategy` and is registered via a decorator. Agents are registered in the same way via `Agent.register(...)`. Strategies are configured through `strategies/predefined_strategies.json`, which defines the workflow, agent, model, optional provider, prompts, optional persistent instructions, and parameters for each strategy.\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:350:If you want to run an existing workflow with a different model or tuned parameters, add a new entry to `strategies/predefined_strategies.json`. Reuse the same `workflow` and `agent` as the base strategy, and differentiate by appending a space and a descriptor to the name:\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:356:  \"agent\": \"pi\",\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:364:  \"persistent-instructions\": \"prompt_templates/persistent/default_agent_rules.md\",\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:374:The strategy name is just a lookup key for the JSON entry. The workflow and agent implementations are resolved from the `workflow` and `agent` fields, so `basic_iterative aggressive` can still point at the `basic_iterative` workflow without any code changes.\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:376:For coding agents that support selecting an LLM backend separately from the model identifier, add a top-level `provider` field to the strategy entry. For example, Pi strategies that should run through OpenRouter can set `\"provider\": \"openrouter\"`.\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:390:1. **Add a strategy entry** to `strategies/predefined_strategies.json` with the matching workflow, agent, prompts, and parameters.\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:403:       def run(self, agent, **kwargs):\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:418:The `dynamic_access_iterative` workflow improves metadata accuracy by using the `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport` Gradle task to identify which dynamic-access call sites (reflection, JNI, resources, serialization) are not yet covered by the generated tests. Instead of generating tests blindly, the workflow iterates class-by-class, sending the agent targeted prompts with the exact uncovered call sites for each class. After each attempt, the report is regenerated and coverage deltas are computed to decide whether to retry the same class or move on.\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:424:Dynamic-access strategies can optionally download library source code, upstream tests, and/or documentation as read-only agent context. This is configured per strategy via the `source-context-types` parameter in `predefined_strategies.json`. Available types are `main`, `test`, and `documentation`. The artifacts are downloaded from URLs in the library's `index.json` (populated by the `populateArtifactURLs` Gradle task) and extracted to `local_repositories/source_context/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/`.\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:462:  [--reachability-metadata-path /path/to/graalvm-reachability-metadata] \\\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:473:  [--reachability-metadata-path /path/to/graalvm-reachability-metadata] \\\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:483:  python3 ai_workflows/fix_javac_fail.py --coordinates <group:artifact:old> --new-version <newVersion> [--reachability-metadata-path <reach-meta-repo>] [--metrics-repo-path <metrics-repo>] [--docs-path <docs>] [--strategy-name NAME]\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:485:  python3 ai_workflows/add_new_library_support.py --coordinates <group:artifact:version> [--reachability-metadata-path <reach-meta-repo>] [--metrics-repo-path <metrics-repo>] [--docs-path <docs>]\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:487:  python3 git_scripts/make_pr_javac_fix.py --coordinates <group:artifact:old> --new-version <newVersion> [--reachability-metadata-path <reach-meta-repo>] [--metrics-repo-path <metrics-repo-root>]\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:489:  python3 git_scripts/make_pr_new_library_support.py --coordinates <group:artifact:version> [--reachability-metadata-path <reach-meta-repo>] [--metrics-repo-root <metrics-repo-root>]\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:491:  python3 complete_pipelines/fix_javac_create_pr.py --coordinates <group:artifact:old> --new-version <newVersion> [--reachability-metadata-path <reach-meta-repo>] [--metrics-repo-path <metrics-repo>] [--docs-path <docs>] [--strategy-name NAME]\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:493:  python3 complete_pipelines/add_new_library_support_create_pr.py --coordinates <coordinates> [--reachability-metadata-path <reach-meta-repo>] [--metrics-repo-path <metrics-repo>] [--docs-path <docs>] [--strategy-name NAME]\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:495:  python3 utility_scripts/count_reachability_entries.py /path/to/reachability-metadata.json\nforge/AGENTS.md:3:Minimal guidelines for automation agents contributing to this repository.\nforge/AGENTS.md:34:- If the change is reusable across workflows, agents, or pipelines, move it to a shared module instead of copying it into a workflow script.\nforge/AGENTS.md:35:- If the change only alters wording or agent instructions, prefer `prompt_templates/` or `strategies/predefined_strategies.json` over Python logic.\nforge/AGENTS.md:38:- `forge_metadata.py`: 